Horrible!! And that is giving them the benefit of the doubt! I was first introduced to Flaco’s Tacos years ago when me and some co-workers used to go to the location near the Chicago redline stop. I don’t believe it is there anymore, although I could be wrong, it has been some years since I was over there. Anyway, their food was always good. The customer service excellent and the drinks strong. At this Granville location the drinks are strong, but everything else lacks! I should have known it wouldn’t be good because no one was in there ordering. 1) The tacos were all COLD! As if they were pre-made, refrigerated, and then warmed up slightly in a microwave. Don’t even try that bs about that’s how tacos are done because I have NEVER eaten a cold taco from a restaurant. 2) the shrimp taco aside from being cold, the shrimp was scorched. Like dang. Did you burn this yesterday and use it for my taco today? I should mention only half of the shrimp on my taco was burnt...the other two pieces were okay. 3) The carnitas taco lacked any flavor on the meat. Like none. Zero. It had way too much cheese...trying to cover up the fact that there are barely any of the other ingredients on this taco? Perhaps. But overall it was like eating boiled pork on a cold dry shell. Not much else going on here. 4) the fish taco was the worst!! The fish was so over cooked and hard, that I bit down on a really dry, hard piece, and almost broke a damn tooth! You can see in the pictures that the fish was so dried out it was hard, inedible, and basically there is no moisture. You couldn’t even chew it like jerky!! The flavor was bland to say the least. I mean there was nothing good to say about the food at all. This taco, like the others, was cold! 4) The saving grace was my mango margarita. It was good and cold and strong!! The downside here though, I barely got any mango flavor. At least the alcohol will help me to forget how bad the food was...if only for a little bit. Overall, you can and SHOULD skip this place. There are much better options for tacos that will not make excuses about serving a cold inedible taco. I would only go to this place to stop in for a drink or two, on my way to get much better tacos/food from somewhere else. You should take my advice, and do the same. It’s not worth the money to even try eating here!
